H0.text: What is the name of the musical instrument that is the Bass of the Oboe family. Cor Anglais

H1.text: What is the name of the musical instrument that is the Bass of the Oboe family. Heckelphone

H2.text: What is the name of the musical instrument that is the Bass of the Oboe family. Dulcian

H3.text: What is the name of the musical instrument that is the Bass of the Oboe family. Basoon

A4.text: The word bassoon comes from French basson and from Italian bassone

A5.text: Documentary: The Production of a Bassoon by Francois de Rudder

A7.text: The most widely known and used today is the cor anglais (English horn), the alto member of the family.

A8.text: Similar to the bass oboe is the more powerful heckelphone, which has a wider bore and larger tone than the baritone oboe.
